    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-11-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-30T22:31:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Accurate Crime Trends for Schools Act or the ACT for Schools Act - Directs the Attorney General to study and report to the appropriate congressional committees on the feasibility of expanding the National Incident-Based Reporting System to include information on the occurrence of school-related crime in elementary and secondary schools.</p> <p>Requires the study to identify and evaluate methods for collecting and reporting such information.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
